  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paul’s Greeting to the Galatians"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Paul, an apostle—sent not from men nor by man, but by Jesus Christ and God the Father, who raised Him from the dead—"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "and all the brothers with me,",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "To the churches of Galatia:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,",
          {
            "noteId": 2090
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "who gave Himself for our sins to rescue us from the present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "No Other Gospel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "I am amazed how quickly you are deserting the One who called you by the grace of Christ and are turning to a different gospel—"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "which is not even a gospel. Evidently some people are troubling you and trying to distort the gospel of Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "But even if we or an angel from heaven should preach a gospel contrary to the one we preached to you, let him be under a curse!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "As we have said before, so now I say again: If anyone is preaching to you a gospel contrary to the one you received, let him be under a curse!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paul Preaches the Gospel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Am I now seeking the approval of men, or of God? Or am I striving to please men? If I were still trying to please men, I would not be a servant of Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For I certify to you, brothers, that the gospel I preached was not devised by man.",
          {
            "noteId": 2091
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "I did not receive it from any man, nor was I taught it; rather, I received it by revelation from Jesus Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "For you have heard of my former way of life in Judaism, how severely I persecuted the church of God and tried to destroy it."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "I was advancing in Judaism beyond many of my contemporaries and was extremely zealous for the traditions of my fathers."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "But when God, who set me apart from my mother’s womb and called me by His grace, was pleased"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "to reveal His Son in me so that I might preach Him among the Gentiles, I did not rush to consult with flesh and blood,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "nor did I go up to Jerusalem to the apostles who came before me, but I went into Arabia and later returned to Damascus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Only after three years did I go up to Jerusalem to confer with Cephas,",
          {
            "noteId": 2092
          },
          "and I stayed with him fifteen days."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "But I saw none of the other apostles except James, the Lord’s brother."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "I assure you before God that what I am writing to you is no lie."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Later I went to the regions of Syria and Cilicia."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "I was personally unknown, however, to the churches of Judea that are in Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "They only heard the account: “The man who formerly persecuted us is now preaching the faith he once tried to destroy.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "And they glorified God because of me."
        ]
      }
    ],
